The jurisdiction given the Fasces six,

I well remember how he used to tell

That though he many offices had borne

None pleased him more than did his Tuscan sway. For not the charge of the Sacred Largesses,

Great though it were, nor the authority

Of Quaestorship, had gratified him more.

His love, bent toward the Tuscans‚ did not shrink From yielding but a secondary place

To the Prefectureship, if this might be.

Nor erred he, dear as much himself to them Whom he approved. Their mutual regards

Raise an undying song of gratitude.

How all-consistent was he and how mild

Old men from their remembrance tell their sons. That from my father’s fame I have not fallen They are glad, and welcome me with two-sold zeal.
